I"^<p>Did half an hour of Javascript exercises on <a href="jschallenger.com">jschallenger.com</a>. <!--more--></p>

<p>One of the more interesting things I learned today was that you can use the ternary operator to make code more succinct.</p>

<p>Instead of</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>function Compare() {
    if (a &lt; b) {
        return a 
    } else {
        return b
    }
}

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You could just write</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">return a &lt; b ? a : b</code></p>
:ET